content.name: Yoga For Legs
content.description: Leg-strengthening yoga poses for beginners. Your legs support you in everyday activity and need to be strong to power through competition. Standing yoga poses will build lower-body power and flexibility in your quadriceps, hamstrings, and calves.

content.name: Yoga For Hips
content.description: Hip-opening yoga poses for beginners. Sitting for extensive periods will cause the muscles to relax and deactivate resulting in tight hips and shorter running strides when the time come to play. These poses will loosen tight hips, improve your range of motion and circulation, and alleviate back pain.

content.name: Yoga For Back
content.description: Back-strengthening yoga poses for beginners. Back pain often occurs because something is off in the way your spinal joints, muscles, discs, and nerves fit together and move. These poses are great for pain relief but are significantly more important for preventative care for these types of issues.

content.name: Yoga For Hamstrings
content.description: Hamstring-stretching yoga poses for beginners. Hamstrings can get shorter or tight when you sit too much or when you over train your quads without counter stretching. When this happens, the hamstrings begin to pull down on the sit bones, making the pelvis and hips tight while flattening the low back curvature in your lumbar area. These poses will help to counter act these effects and prolong your career as an athlete.

content.name: Yoga For Shoulders
content.description: Shoulder-relief yoga poses for beginners. Pain in the shoulder can have many potential causes, including muscle injury and torn ligaments. Shoulder stretches are an amazing way to release tension in your head and neck while rehabbing any injuries or pain.
